Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @Carrot{2}(trimmed) and @Parsnip{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop both into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Chop the @Baking Potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop the carrots and parsnip onto another large baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the red onion and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour in the @Water for the Jus{150%ml} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @Red Wine Jus Paste{15%g}, then reduce the heat to medium.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and set aside.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of baking paper or cling film. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a saucepan until it's 1-2cm thick. Season with salt and pepper.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Dried Rosemary{1%sachet}, @Plain Flour{1.5%tbsp} and a pinch of salt. Add the chicken breasts and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Sprinkle the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} over the chicken, pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Set aside to allow the cheese to melt.

Meanwhile, halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, reheat the onion gravy if needed. Drizzle the @Honey{1%tbsp} over the carrots and parsnip. Toss to coat.

Spread the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases. Top with the rosemary chicken and spoon over the gravy. Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve the roasted potatoes, carrots and parsnip batons alongside. Enjoy!